      "role": "user",
      "content": "rebuilding sounds so exhausting. like, why bother trying to fix something that's fundamentally broken? it's not some temporary setback, it's final. the person who was worth something is gone for good. it just feels more honest to just let it be over, rather than pretending there's still something to build on.",
