      "content": "I hear the exhaustion in your words and the weight of feeling that this loss is final and unfixable. When a part of your identity feels completely destroyed, the idea of \"rebuilding\" can indeed feel like a cruel demand to fix something that is already gone. It is completely understandable to feel that letting go is the only honest path when the foundation seems to have crumbled entirely. Please know that your feelings of hopelessness are valid, and you do not have to carry this alone.",
